If we add here also the fiscal reasons associated with the lack of trust in the national currency, as well as the deteriorating prospects for economic growth, by the end of this year, inflation may well exceed 8%.
Alexander Razuvaev, Director of the Analytical Department "Alpari"
Inflation sometimes reached 20-30% per month, in zero it was also above the current level, another matter that it was then compensated for by rapid economic growth.
I think that by the end of the year, inflation will be 8-8.5%.
Platon Magut, Asset Manager of Maguta Foundation
The external factor associated with sanctions against Russia is still being successfully constrained, but if there is a further increase in pressure, primarily on the financial sector - this can lead to certain difficulties and increase the inflation expectations of the population, which are usually traditionally manifested in the purchases of cash in order to secure their savings.
It can be assumed that the government, the Central Bank of the Russian Federation and the Ministry of Finance will try to soften the smooth weakening of the ruble, both by market methods and state regulation.
But price growth begins traditionally after a summer lull and, perhaps, this fall will become more tangible.
