Calculation of estimates of construction facilities in the Russian Federation will take place in a new way
Issues of pricing, regulation of the construction industry, as well as the problems of connection to the networks, the Federal Antimonopoly Service takes special control.
Under the FAS, an expert council for the development of competition in the construction sector was created.
At its meeting, the head of the department of control of housing and communal services, construction and natural resources of the FAS Vadim Solovyov said that "today's calculation of the estimates of construction facilities is absolutely incomprehensible."
The regulatory framework makes pricing opaque and can lead to an unreasonable price of construction, according to the FAS.
And they propose the cost of construction of state-owned facilities at the design stage to determine on the basis of market prices of constructive solutions instead of the estimated standards and single prices for technological operations used today.
These proposals have been made on the road map and are under consideration in the Minstroy.
"The replacement of traditional estimated documentation in construction with the calculations of constructive elements should lead to less corruption in the industry," explained RGB Vadim Solovyov.
After all, now the estimate counts every bolt and nut, and it is not always possible to check everything, so sometimes in the documentation unscrupulous construction companies can bury "whole tractors."
In the Ministry of Construction with the FAS agree.
"The first developments on the transition to the calculation of the cost on constructive elements already exist: methods have been developed to calculate the prices for constructive solutions, to prepare estimates for these indicators," said Elena Zhukova, Head of the Department of Urban Development and Architecture of the Ministry of Construction of the Ministry of Construction.
The field of road construction has been chosen as a pilot.
However, experts believe that the problem is much more serious.
According to RGB, the head of the construction company "Profi-invest" Anatoly Demianko, the estimated standards have long been outdated, but another mechanism has not yet been proposed to the business.
"As for the proposed calculations on constructive elements, in practice, this is difficult to implement, since completely different technologies are often used in the construction of buildings," he said.
It is no secret that the construction market is developing largely due to the state order.
According to the Chairman of the Board of NP "Expert community of professionals of state order" Ekaterina Lezina, today the state is the most solvent customer.
Deputy Director for Engineering of the industry center of capital construction of Rosatom Vladimir Malakhov drew attention to the fact that today the market is conditionally divided into companies that have access to the portfolio of contracts, and to companies that own monopoly competencies and do not allow competitors on this field.
He believes that the creation of a transparent market is possible only if access to contracts will be as protected as possible from someone's control.
At the expert council, it was proposed to form a system of state order in such a way that the same performer is not entitled to receive more than one contract worth more than 1 billion rubles. or several contracts worth more than 1 billion rubles.
The Ministry of Construction believes that this approach should be evaluated in terms of the impact on business, as well as the effectiveness of construction management.
As explained by Elena Zhukova, in this case it will be necessary to give the customer the functions of the general contractor, which will lead to an increase in the staff of the customer and budget expenditures for its maintenance.
At the same time, the customer's specialists will have the knowledge to assess the quality of the work performed by contractors, as well as their safety.
Often, with such a breakdown, it will be necessary to determine who will be responsible for the security of the object as a whole.
In addition, this approach may lead to the outflow of highly qualified participants in public procurement due to the lack of interest in obtaining a state order for an incomplete amount of work and a small amount of the contract.
Deputy head of the expert and consulting center of the Institute of Procurement Alexander Evstashenkov believes that now the procedure of the state order has turned into a business game for the attentiveness of the contractor.
And he gave such an example: "the participant when filling out the application must specify "specific indicators" without specifying the words: "or the equivalent," "must be," "from," "more," "less," "similate," "or," "type," "similar type," "not lower," "below," "further," "can be" "may have," "can be," "earlier," "early," "not earlier," "not allowed."
Thus, customers often abuse their right to establish requirements for the content of the application submitted by contractors.
Another problem of 44-FZ, according to Evstashenkov, was the need to assess at the stage of applying the quality of work through the "paper" offer of the participant.
Considering the application of the participant, you can really evaluate only the qualifications of the contractor, but not the quality of the work, the performance of which has not even begun, - the expert believes.
The quality of the work can be estimated only when they are accepted.
The expert council also proposed to transfer the margin income from the upper to the lower echelon, so that intermediate contractors would disappear.
Chairman of the expert council, State Secretary, Deputy Head of the FAS Andrei Tsarikovsky believes that this is not worth doing, as the general contractor should be responsible for the order.
Otherwise, it will turn out, as in the famous reprisal of Arkady Raikin "Atelier": "Is there a claim to the buttons?"
