Thousands of Israeli children in the territories near the Gaza Strip went to school again on Monday after spending the summer in bomb shelters, when rockets and mines fell on their settlements during the 50-day war between Israel and Hamas, while schools in the Gaza Strip remained closed during the territory recovering from the fighting.
