All civil servants must appear at identification centres within the next two weeks to ensure that their data is collected through a biometric registration procedure, the government said.
Anyone who does not do this without a good reason will be erased from the payroll, it reports.
"This procedure will significantly contribute to the rationalization of the public service, identifying the actual number of civil servants, and will also be used to clear the payroll at both levels of the government - hence put an end to the problem of "invisible workers," said Anne Weigur, Secretary of the Cabinet of Ministers of Planning and Structuring.
