The Ministry of Economic Development wants to accelerate the growth of the electric car market
This week, the Ministry of Economic Development will submit to the government a comprehensive plan for the development of environmentally friendly transport in Russia, said Deputy Director of the Department of the Ministry Oleg Pluzhnikov at a round table, which was held by "Vedomosti" at the Moscow Motor Show - 2014.
The plan was drawn up on behalf of the government, one of the main goals is to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
It is expected that the document will be adopted in late September - early October, says Pluzhnikov, the proposed measures relate to electric vehicles and hybrids - a plan for the development of vehicles on gas engine fuel in Russia already exists.
The plan (there is a copy of the "Vedomosti") is designed for 2014-2017.
It is necessary to develop criteria for the assessment of electric and hybrid transport and to decide how to stimulate the use and production of environmentally friendly vehicles.
The report to the government, which will describe tax and customs measures to support electric transport, will be prepared by December 2014; a scheme for preferential lending and preferential leasing will appear by April 2015; and proposals for lowering the price of machines, stimulating localization and creation of service infrastructure will be developed by October 2015.
In 2014-2015 It is planned to make changes to the regulations in order to facilitate the conditions for the construction of charging infrastructure (at parking lots, petrol stations, etc.).
In addition, federal officials intend to hold in 2015. formulate proposals for regional authorities that they also stimulate the use of environmentally friendly transport - in the form of providing it with benefits when driving and parking, for example; and by February 2016. - and proposals for the expansion of public procurement of such transport.
Finally, the Ministry of Economic Development is already by October 2014. will include in the list of indicators of assessment of the activities of regional authorities, the criteria reflecting the effectiveness of support for the production of environmentally friendly transport, the development of charging infrastructure.
The market of electric cars in Russia is only being formed - in 2013. About 100 electric vehicles have been sold in the country.
In the early 2014. zeroed import duty on electric cars, so sales will amount to about 500 units, predicts chief executive of Mitsubishi Motors in Russia Andrey Pankov.
But the five-fold growth does not make electric cars any noticeable: in 2013. In Russia, according to the Association of European Businesses, 2.78 million passenger and light commercial vehicles have been sold.
So far, only Mitsubishi Motors imports electric vehicles to Russia.
Start imports are prepared by Renault - the company focuses primarily on corporate customers, says the director of strategic planning and partnerships Renault in Russia Nicolas Remiz.
Most other manufacturers of electric transport took a wait-and-see position in relation to Russia.
There are also developments of electric vehicles in Russian manufacturers - "," GAZ, ," but the release is minuscule.
For example, in January-July 2014, according to ASM-holding, AvtoVAZ produced 30 electric vehicles.
Demand is low due to the high cost of electric vehicles, admits the director of "AvtoVAZ" in engineering Sergey Amanov, without state support, there will be no breakthrough in this segment.
The development of the Russian market of electric vehicles in addition to the high cost of cars (the electric cars that are sold in Russia, on average, is twice as expensive as analogues with internal combustion engines) restrains the underdevelopment of the charging infrastructure (refuelling units), the general director of "AUTOSTAT" Sergey Tselikov.
Due to the high cost and low rates of lower cost of electric vehicles in the next 3-4 years will remain a niche segment of the Russian market, predicts the editor-in-chief of Avtorev Mikhail Podrozhansky, Tselikov agrees with him.
Automakers, on the contrary, say that some models of electric vehicles are already close to the cost of conventional cars.
The Russian market of electric vehicles has good prospects, the main thing is to inspire confidence in consumers that "electricity" is real; this, in particular, will be facilitated by the emergence of new charging stations, emphasizes the president of the BMW group in Russia Wolfgang Schlimme.
Such infrastructure projects are being implemented, for example, by the state-owned company Rosseti: several stations have been built in Moscow, about 80 more will appear.
Negotiations on the construction of a gas station network are also being conducted with other regions.
According to the director of the department of "Rosseti" Vladimir Sofyin, the company believes in the market of electric vehicles and is ready to build refueling throughout the country, but there are problems: a small number of electric vehicles in the country and the lack of a single standard for charging electric vehicles of various brands.
In addition, "Rosseti" as a grid company do not have the right to engage in the sale of electricity, the opportunity to do this in relation to charging electric vehicles is being worked out.
Pankiv considers the most effective measure of state support for the formation of the electric vehicle market in Russia, the zeroing of customs duties.
The zero rate will be valid until the end of 2014, the possibility of its extension, expansion of the preferential list is being considered.
The replacement of the transport tax on the environmental (the idea is being discussed and concerns all machines) will also support the market, but not as tangible as customs preferences, according to Pankow.
The transport tax in Russia is small, says Pankov, unlike, for example, Norway, where the tax cuts led to a sharp increase in sales of electric cars - now they account for 12% of the market.
In Russia, incentive measures are needed for car owners, for example, free parking in the city center (as already done in Moscow), Pankow, or the possibility of moving electric cars on the allocated lanes, which is not yet in Russia.
