Twitter has become more interesting for new users
The microblogging service Twitter has changed the process of registering users to quickly involve new participants in active interaction with the platform.
This measure should reduce the number of people who have abandoned their microblogging.
Now, new Twitter users will be viewing during the registration a large number of recommended accounts with the service to immediately make their reading.
Recommendations are drawn up on the basis of the interests indicated in the registration of interests.
At the same time, Twitter automatically checks a subscription box for all automatically selected accounts.
Because of this, the user will have to personally remove the checkboxes, so as not to read those who are not interested in him.
If earlier users of the microblogging service saw only the avatars of recommended users, now Twitter is displaying a sample of one of the blogger's popular tweets to help make an impression of a person.
This is the biggest change in the Twitter registration page in the last three years.
Recently, Twitter has been actively working on the modernization of the service.
Such activity is primarily associated with the continued attempts of the service to achieve breakeven.
In 2014, the microblogging service faced a slowdown in the growth of the user base and a drop in reader activity.
The company is currently in desperate need of more consumers loyal to the resource, who, once in time, would remain for a long time.
This is the only way to ensure a stable flow of advertising tools.
