Mathematical Analysis is sold for $93.49 in second-hand form at Chegg.com.
Matt Caseday, 25, a fourth-year student at Brigham Young University, says he paid 42 cents at Amazon.com for a used copy of the textbook "Strategic Media Solutions: Understanding the Business Side of the Advertising Business."
The book was sold for $48 new.
Teachers, such as Ingrid Bracies, director of College Without Walls at the University of Massachusetts at Emherst, invites students to clarify to their professors whether they can not use previous editions.
Sometimes the updates are insignificant for classes.
In such cases, the old editions can often be found for a very small fraction of the cost of the last edition.
In addition to the sites Chegg and Amazon, Half.com, owned by "eBay Inc.," is a popular alternative for buying used books.
Car rental
You should think about getting textbooks for rent, if you treat them well enough, do not forget to return them and do not want to keep them after the course is completed.
You can save more than 80% of the cost of a new book.
For example, one student was able to rent a "Mathematical Analysis" for a semester for about $20.
Find out the rules of the store where you take books, including any fines that you can write out for notes, underlines and damage.
If you rent a book, remember: if you do not return the book, fines can even exceed the cost of a new copy.
E-books
E-books instead of traditional textbooks - another option.
Sometimes such books are rented, acquiring an electronic license for a certain period from distributors, for example, Amazon.com, Chegg and Barnes & Noble Inc.
Rent "Mathematical analysis" on the website Chegg.com for six months will cost about $61.
