"Europrotocol" instead of the traffic police
Payments on the casco can be received without a certificate of traffic police - so the Central Bank intends to stimulate the introduction of the "Europrotocol" in Russia.
The Bank of Russia has developed a draft of instructions, according to which from September 1 of this year to receive payments on the Casco, the insured motorist will be able to do without a traffic police certificate.
We are talking, however, only about those cases when the accident was issued according to the "Europrotocol" without the participation of the road police.
That is, if only two cars participated in the accident, there are no physically injured persons, the damage does not exceed the established limit and both drivers reached agreement on the issue of who is the culprit of the accident.
From August 2, the limit of payments on the "Europrotocol" is 50 thousand. from October 1 in Moscow, St. Petersburg, as well as in the Moscow and Leningrad regions, it will be increased to 400 thousand. The rub.
The bottom line is that often even with minor damage, in a situation where an accident can be issued by "Europrotocol," drivers who got into an accident, cause traffic police.
After all, in the presence of a casco policy, it was impossible to receive compensation for it without a certificate of traffic police.
The parameters prescribed in the draft instructions are designed to eliminate this obstacle to the introduction of the "Europrototocol" in Russia.
According to them, the maximum payment for the casco in connection with the accident, issued without traffic police officers, should not be lower than the limit on the "Europrotocol."
But at the same time, it cannot be higher than the limit defined in the casco insurance contract.
The idea, of course, is useful and theoretically able to unload both traffic police officers and roads.
